1 (b) For a vacancy in the office of supreme court justice caused by the end of the justice's term, the
2 nomination committee shall provide to the governor the names of at least three but no more than five qualified
3 nominees at least 60 days prior to the end of the justice's term. The the governor shall appoint a justice from
4 those names within 60 days after receiving the names. If the nomination committee fails to provide at least
5 three qualified nominees by the required date, the governor shall appoint an individual from a list of 10
6 nominees chosen by lottery from a full list of qualified nominees. The full list of qualified nominees must be
7 created using a method determined by the nomination committee a list of two or more persons nominated by
8 the nomination committee.
9 (c) For a vacancy in the office of supreme court justice caused by any other reason, the
10 nomination committee shall provide to the governor the names of at least three but no more than five qualified
11 nominees within 60 days after receiving notification of the vacancy from the chief justice of the supreme court.
12 The governor shall appoint a justice from those names within 60 days after receiving the names. If the
13 nomination committee fails to provide at least three qualified nominees by the required date, the governor shall
14 appoint an individual from a list of 10 nominees chosen by lottery from a full list of qualified nominees. The full
15 list of qualified nominees must be created using a method determined by the nomination committee.
16 (d) Appointments of supreme court justices made under this subsection (3) shall be subject to
17 confirmation by the senate, as provided in law.
18 (e)(c) A supreme court justice shall serve until the expiration of the term for which the justice was
19 appointed or until the expiration of the term of the justice's predecessor if the appointment was to fill an
20 unexpired term. At the general election ballot preceding the expiration of the justice's term, the justice must be
21 placed on the general election to allow the voters of the state to approve or reject the justice. The office of a
22 supreme court justice becomes vacant 90 days after the election at which the justice is rejected by a majority of
23 those voting on the question or for which the justice fails to file a declaration of candidacy to stand in the
24 retention election.
